docs {
  # User Management v2.0

  Staff user lifecycle (CLAUDE.md §-users, MIGRATION-PLAN.md §9). Mounted under
  `users/manage` so it never collides with the legacy person/patient routes.

  **Identity** lives on the platform `Person` (Aadhaar encrypted at rest);
  **employment** (sequential `USR-00001` code, Internal/External type, role,
  tenant-global status) lives on `TenantStaffMembership`; **branch assignments**
  (per-branch status + default work-area module) on `UserBranchProfile`; and
  **permissions** are module-grouped per (user + branch) in
  `user_branch_permissions`.

  ## Suggested order

  1. **Branches → Set Branch Modules** — enable the work-area modules at the
     branch first (the default module + permission modal only show enabled ones).
  2. **Create User** — captures `manageUserId` + `manageUserCode`.
  3. **Assign Branches** / **Update Branch Assignment** — multi-branch, default
     branch, per-branch status, default module.
  4. **Get / Update Branch Permissions** — module-grouped grants.
  5. **Deactivate / Activate User** — tenant-global on/off (login backstop).
  6. **List Users / Get User / List Profile Permissions** — read screens.

  Run **Business Auth → Login** first (as a `business_admin`) so
  `businessAccessToken` is populated.
}
